The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 World Briefs

 Lanka deadlock 

 Kilinochchi, Dec. 17 (Reuters): Tamil Tiger rebels today rejected a government offer to hold talks in Asia aimed at averting a return to civil war, insisting any meeting should be hosted by peace broker Norway. 

 President Mahinda Rajapakse has offered to meet the rebels for talks in any Asian country, but not in Europe. 

 Iraq polls 

 Baghdad (Reuters): The main Sunni alliance that contested Iraqs election said on Saturday it had been a success. 

 Afghan clash 

 Kabul (Reuters): Taliban guerrillas attacked a high school in southern Afghanistan on Saturday, killing a guard and a male teenage student. 

 Bangla raid 

 Dhaka (Reuters): Police in Bangladesh seized bombs and arrested four militants in the second major raid this week on radicals. 




